{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-03-29-how-to-add-alt-text-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add alt text in react js, you can use  with in . It will add alt text in react js. Today, I am going to show you, how to‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add alt text in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">alt</code> with in <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;img/></code>. It will add alt text in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add alt text in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h2>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h2>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 2: Import react component.</h2>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 3: Create a Component.</h2>\n<p>you can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;img src=\"image.jpg\" alt=\"Description of the image\" /></code> and add alt text in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>img src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"image.jpg\"</span> alt<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Description of the image\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Define the add alt text example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">React</code>. and use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;img src=\"image.jpg\" alt=\"Description of the image\" /></code> to add alt text in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">App</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>img src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"image.jpg\"</span> alt<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Description of the image\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">img</code> tag and add alt text in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 315px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f649866f8982fc505b6a5fa95a924a15/6ea66/add-alt-text.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.65822784810127%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRlIAAABXRUJQVlA4IEYAAACQAwCdASoUAA0APtFWpEuoJKOhsAgBABoJQApgAPQKrMZ203YAAP4ntfk/jbGmdOd2bATLCf4mwHnEHJCVpxCUFugA0gAA'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, add, alt text\"\n        title=\"React, add, alt text\"\n        src=\"/static/f649866f8982fc505b6a5fa95a924a15/6ea66/add-alt-text.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f649866f8982fc505b6a5fa95a924a15/81b7c/add-alt-text.webp 158w,\n/static/f649866f8982fc505b6a5fa95a924a15/6ea66/add-alt-text.webp 315w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 315px) 100vw, 315px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n       